  <div id = "rome">
    <h3>Rome</h3>
    <p>An ancient city with a modern twist considered one of the world’s most photogenic cities. Whether you spend your time sightseeing, or watching the world go by in a scenic outdoor cafe, it will be your turn experience your very own Roman Holiday.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "venice">
    <h3>Venice</h3>
    <p>Enjoy a ride in a gondola down one of the world’s oldest waterways — the Grand Canal. A romantic voyage showcasing Italy’s old world charm. Shop in one of the best fashion capitals of the world.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "florence">
    <h3>Florence</h3>
    <p>Home to the Duomo, the capital of Tuscany boasts remarkable works of art such as “The David” and “The Birth of Venus. Provides some of the best night-life locations in the country.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "pisa">
    <h3>Pisa</h3>
    <p>Pisa is a city in Italy’s Tuscany region best known for its iconic Leaning Tower. Already tilting when it was completed in 1372, the 56m white-marble cylinder is the bell tower of the Romanesque, striped-marble cathedral that rises next to it in the Piazza dei Miracoli.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "naples">
    <h3>Naples</h3>
    <p>Naples, a city in southern Italy, sits on the Bay of Naples. Nearby is Mount Vesuvius, the still-active volcano that destroyed nearby Roman town Pompeii.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "pompeii">
    <h3>Pompeii</h3>
    <p>Pompeii is a vast archaeological site located in southern Italy’s Campania region. Once a thriving and sophisticated Roman city, Pompeii was buried in meters of ash and pumice after the catastrophic eruption of Mount Vesuvius in 79 A.D.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "cinque-terre">
    <h3>Cinque Terre</h3>
    <p>Cinque Terre is a string of centuries-old seaside villages on the rugged Italian Riviera coastline. In each of the 5 towns, colorful houses and vineyards cling to steep terraces, harbors are filled with fishing boats and trattorias turn out seafood specialties along with the Liguria region’s famous sauce, pesto.</p>
  </div>

  <div id = "milan">
    <h3>Milan</h3>
    <p>Milan, a metropolis in Italy’s northern Lombardy region, is a global capital of fashion and design. Home to the national stock exchange, it’s a financial hub also known for its high-end restaurants and shops.</p>
  </div>
